@kustomjourney.id SHOW & SELL OPEN SUBMISSION:
Kustomtoyst Exhibition
Deadline: 1 October 2025

Kustomtoys Exhibition adalah area Show & Sell yang menampilkan karya mainan hasil kreasi para toys maker. Pameran ini membuka kesempatan bagi para kreator untuk memajang karya dalam berbagai kategori, seperti Upcycle Toys, Art Toys, Designer Toys, dan Urban Toys. Setiap peserta diperbolehkan mendaftarkan lebih dari satu karya, sehingga dapat menampilkan beragam eksplorasi dan karakter dari mainan yang mereka buat dengan menggunakan bahan apapun, seperti vinyl, resin, kain, upcycle atau mainan bekas dan dengan tanpa ada batasan genre.

Jadi, buat kamu-kamu yang merasa sudah siap untuk majang toysnya di Kustom Journey tahun ini, langsung lesgow aja daftar di link yang ada di Bio kami.

Karya apapun akan tetap melalui proses kurasi oleh tim Rolliemonkie. Karya yang lolos kurasi, harus sudah sampai di kantor Rolliemonkie pada tanggal 1 Oktober 2025.

Semua karya yang lolos kurasi, bakalan kami pajang di:

adidas Y-3 Gendo Superstar (Black, Size 10.5)

When Yohji Yamamoto first partnered with adidas in 2002 to launch Y-3, it redefined how sportswear and high fashion could intersect. Two decades later, the Gendo Superstar pushed that vision into radical new territory.

Unveiled during Paris Fashion Week in 2022, the Gendo transformed the iconic adidas Superstar into a piece of wearable architecture. The shoe retained its leather upper and shell-toe heritage, but sat atop a hollowed-out, sculptural plate designed to â€œelevateâ€ the wearer â€” literally and conceptually. Its open-arch platform blurred the line between sneaker and object, a bold experiment that drew coverage from Highsnobiety, Hypebeast, and Vogue, with headlines framing it as one of the most daring sneaker designs of the year.

The Gendo Superstar wasnâ€™t made for mass wear. Its limited release, avant-garde silhouette, and high price point made it instantly polarizing â€” celebrated by collectors of Yohji Yamamotoâ€™s work and fashion-forward sneakerheads, while bewildering traditionalists. Today, it stands as one of the most striking examples of Y-3â€™s philosophy: challenging expectations while preserving the DNA of adidasâ€™ most iconic sneaker.
